      • sortLog

        public static java.lang.String sortLog​(java.lang.String log)
        This method is used to sort log actions by timestamp.

        The method extracts actions from the log into the List<String> and sort them. A newline symbol is added to each element of the list and the list is transformed into the string log with sorted actions.

        Parameters:
        log - the log that contains input actions.
        Returns:
        sorted log

      • identifyPasteAction

        public static java.lang.String identifyPasteAction​(java.lang.String log)
        Finds patterns that contain "editCell" or "editRange" actions after any of "copy" actions and changes "editCell" or "editRange" actions to "pasteIntoCell" and "pasteIntoRange" actions respectively.

        The method contains cellRegex, rangeRegex and chromeRegex regular expressions. cellRegex corresponds to the case when there are "copyCell" action, any number of actions and "editCell" action which target.value is equal to "copyCell" action content (\\4). rangeRegex corresponds to the case when there are "copyRange" action, any number of actions and "editRange" action which target.value is equal to "copyRange" action content (\\8). chromeRegex corresponds to the case when there is Chrome "copy" action, any number of actions and "editCell" action which target.value is equal to "copy" action content (\\4). If the log contains a pattern that matches cellRegex regular expressions, the method will replace "editCell" action from the pattern to "pasteIntoCell", and if the log contains rangeRegex regular expression the method will replace "editRange" action from the pattern to "pasteIntoRange" action.

        Parameters:
        log - the log that contains input actions.
        Returns:
        log with replaced "editCell" or "editRange" action with "pasteIntoCell" or "pasteIntoRange" actions.

      • mergeNavigationCellCopy

        public static java.lang.String mergeNavigationCellCopy​(java.lang.String log)
        Merges Excel navigation cell actions and OS-Clipboard "copy" actions then deletes all "getRange" and "getCell" actions.

        The method contains getCellRegex, getRangeRegex and editCellRegex regular expressions that correspond to the case when there are any number of actions except "editCell", "getRange" and "getCell" between "getCell" action, "getRange" action and "editCell" action respectively and "copy" action. If the log contains pattern that matches any of these regular expressions, the method will replace the pattern with new action: for getCellRegex and editCellRegex will bew created "copyCell" action and for getRangeRegex "copyRange" action. The method will be called again until there is a pattern that matches any of these regular expressions. After replacing defined patterns, the method removes all "getCell" and "getRange" actions.

        Parameters:
        log - the log that contains input actions.
        Returns:
        log with merged "editCell", "getRange" and "getCell" actions and OS-Clipboard "copy" action.

      • deleteChromeClipboardCopy

        public static java.lang.String deleteChromeClipboardCopy​(java.lang.String log)
        Deletes OS-Clipboard "copy" action if it is preceded by Chrome "copy" action.

        $1 is a parameter of String regex that is responsible for Chrome "copy" action. The method will be called again if the log contains other patterns that match String regex until there are none of them.

        Parameters:
        log - the log that contains input actions.
        Returns:
        the log without OS-Clipboard "copy" actions that are preceded by Chrome "copy" actions.
